1
00:00:00,280 --> 00:00:02,040
Mercan doesn't know why Eylül died.

2
00:00:02,840 --> 00:00:07,360
One way or another, Eylül died because of Mercan.

3
00:00:08,000 --> 00:00:09,000
She was murdered...

4
00:00:09,360 --> 00:00:12,680
Instead of making them pay for this, you're still trying to protect Mercan.

5
00:00:13,520 --> 00:00:14,360
I agree.

6
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:16,080
Mercan is off-limits.

7
00:00:16,640 --> 00:00:18,920
Ateş has a huge weak spot for Mercan.

8
00:00:19,480 --> 00:00:22,920
Tomorrow, Mercan might even ask him to let Haydar out of the warehouse.

9
00:00:23,320 --> 00:00:25,400
Our paths were going to cross sooner or later anyway.

10
00:00:26,120 --> 00:00:27,880
It's best not to drag it out.

11
00:00:28,120 --> 00:00:30,520
When the hundred and eighty-seven days are up, I'm leaving.

12
00:00:30,680 --> 00:00:31,880
We'll share the same room

13
00:00:32,160 --> 00:00:34,720
and do whatever is required by the contract.

14
00:00:34,840 --> 00:00:36,440
I'm not following the contract.

15
00:00:36,720 --> 00:00:37,760
I've made my decision.

16
00:00:38,080 --> 00:00:39,760
After the hundred and eighty-seven days are over...

17
00:00:40,680 --> 00:00:41,760
Once you divorce that man...

18
00:00:42,080 --> 00:00:42,760
Marry me.

19
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:44,960
You know I love Ateş very much, Nezir.

20
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:49,200
How will you be happy with someone who loves another?

21
00:00:50,560 --> 00:00:52,040
Nothing is important to me.

22
00:00:54,040 --> 00:00:56,360
Only you matter, Mercan.

23
00:00:56,960 --> 00:00:57,560
Let me think about it.

24
00:00:59,200 --> 00:01:00,240
What the hell are you saying?

25
00:01:00,840 --> 00:01:02,600
What marriage after a hundred and eighty-seven days?

26
00:01:03,120 --> 00:01:05,560
I was telling her to marry me once she gets rid of you.

27
00:01:06,040 --> 00:01:06,640
Don't you interfere!

28
00:01:07,040 --> 00:01:08,080
I already have!

29
00:01:08,760 --> 00:01:10,720
I won't leave you in this man's hands.

30
00:01:12,600 --> 00:01:14,120
When you were jealous of Nezir...

31
00:01:15,160 --> 00:01:17,400
When you stopped Mrs. Müzeyyen just now...

32
00:01:18,040 --> 00:01:21,360
When you picked up the pieces in the kitchen so I wouldn't get hurt…

33
00:01:22,320 --> 00:01:24,640
All of them bore the traces of the love you have for me.

34
00:01:25,040 --> 00:01:27,440
no one can tear you out of my heart.

35
00:01:27,720 --> 00:01:28,960
Neither the anger you feel for my father

36
00:01:30,040 --> 00:01:31,840
nor Mrs. Müzeyyen's hatred can achieve that.

37
00:01:32,280 --> 00:01:34,120
Everyone is going to know everything now.

38
00:01:34,760 --> 00:01:37,080
I'm tired of you wrapping this girl in cotton wool!

39
00:01:37,680 --> 00:01:42,080
She'll know the cost. And at whose expense she lives…

40
00:01:42,920 --> 00:01:43,920
What do you mean?

41
00:01:44,320 --> 00:01:47,560
The kidney you're carrying is Eylül's kidney.

42
00:01:48,640 --> 00:01:51,680
They killed her so you could live!

43
00:03:12,760 --> 00:03:14,600
Eylül died because of you!

44
00:03:24,040 --> 00:03:26,680
Your father sacrificed her so you could live!

45
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:28,600
You're both murderers!

46
00:03:37,440 --> 00:03:39,240
Aslı, enough! Shut up!

47
00:03:39,280 --> 00:03:40,280
It's not enough!

48
00:03:40,880 --> 00:03:43,840
All this pain was suffered because of her.

49
00:03:50,200 --> 00:03:54,000
But to your father, Eylül's life had absolutely no value.

50
00:03:54,560 --> 00:03:56,800
You should be the one lying in that grave, not Eylül.

51
00:04:06,760 --> 00:04:08,120
Aslı, enough!

52
00:04:08,160 --> 00:04:09,000
No!

53
00:04:15,360 --> 00:04:17,680
For his precious princess Mercan to survive...

54
00:04:18,040 --> 00:04:22,800
she was just an expendable, orphaned child.

55
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:24,120
I said enough, Aslı!

56
00:04:34,520 --> 00:04:37,640
Don't you dare think this subject is closed here!

57
00:04:37,680 --> 00:04:39,000
You will pay for what you did!

58
00:04:39,640 --> 00:04:40,440
You will!

59
00:04:56,640 --> 00:04:57,800
(gulps)

60
00:04:58,280 --> 00:04:58,960
She...

61
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:02,120
She's lying, right?

62
00:05:07,480 --> 00:05:08,000
Huh?

63
00:05:16,400 --> 00:05:17,680
I asked you a question!

64
00:05:18,640 --> 00:05:19,800
Answer me!

65
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:22,360
Speak!

66
00:05:23,760 --> 00:05:26,880
Tell me she's lying! Tell me it's not true!

67
00:05:33,480 --> 00:05:36,080
Look at me! In my eyes! Answer me!

68
00:05:36,680 --> 00:05:38,080
Tell me it's not true, come on!

69
00:05:54,120 --> 00:05:57,120
No, no, no, no! No!

70
00:05:57,480 --> 00:05:59,560
No, this can't be true!

71
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:08,000
Eylül couldn't have died because of me!

72
00:06:08,720 --> 00:06:09,520
No!

73
00:06:09,960 --> 00:06:10,560
No!
No!

74
00:06:12,640 --> 00:06:13,160
Get out of my way!

75
00:06:39,120 --> 00:06:39,880
Open the door.

76
00:06:43,760 --> 00:06:46,000
Cemal! I told you to open the door!

77
00:06:47,160 --> 00:06:47,800
Mercan!

78
00:06:48,240 --> 00:06:49,400
What are you doing to my daughter!

79
00:06:50,400 --> 00:06:51,400
Mercan!

80
00:06:52,320 --> 00:06:54,040
Let my daughter go! Ateş!

81
00:06:54,880 --> 00:06:56,760
Cemal! Open the door!

82
00:06:57,720 --> 00:06:59,800
Open this door! I'm telling you to open it! Open it!

83
00:07:02,840 --> 00:07:04,720
Open this door! I'm telling you to open it! Open it!

84
00:07:04,960 --> 00:07:07,360
-Mercan, stop! Don't. -Let go. Let go.

85
00:07:08,560 --> 00:07:09,680
Open this door.

86
00:07:11,680 --> 00:07:13,800
-Open this door! I said open it! -Mercan!

87
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:16,520
If you don't open it, I'll find a way! I'll break it down!

88
00:07:16,560 --> 00:07:19,120
I'll burn it down if I have to! Do you understand? Open this door!

89
00:07:19,160 --> 00:07:20,560
Just stop, get a hold of yourself.

90
00:07:22,480 --> 00:07:23,560
Open this door!

91
00:07:28,120 --> 00:07:30,240
Leave my daughter alone! Ateş!

92
00:07:30,880 --> 00:07:32,120
Ateş! Leave my daughter alone!

93
00:07:33,480 --> 00:07:34,720
-Mercan... -Tell the truth.

94
00:07:35,560 --> 00:07:37,640
Dad, tell the truth! Is all this true!

95
00:07:38,600 --> 00:07:40,640
Did Eylül die because of me!

96
00:07:41,320 --> 00:07:44,160
Answer me! Did you kill her so I could live!

97
00:07:44,200 --> 00:07:45,120
Mercan, please!

98
00:07:46,160 --> 00:07:46,680
Please!

99
00:07:47,920 --> 00:07:49,560
I'm begging you, open this door!

100
00:07:50,720 --> 00:07:52,720
I have to know, don't you understand?

101
00:07:52,760 --> 00:07:54,840
I need to hear everything from him.

102
00:07:59,000 --> 00:07:59,480
Okay.

103
00:08:41,440 --> 00:08:42,760
How did Eylül die?

104
00:08:45,280 --> 00:08:47,320
Why are you digging up old issues?

105
00:08:49,560 --> 00:08:50,720
I asked you a question!

106
00:08:51,160 --> 00:08:52,600
Tell me! How did Eylül die!

107
00:08:58,640 --> 00:08:59,720
Answer me!

108
00:09:00,280 --> 00:09:02,000
Am I carrying her kidney?

109
00:09:02,960 --> 00:09:05,080
Am I alive because of Eylül!

110
00:09:09,680 --> 00:09:10,360
Yes.

111
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:16,120
You are alive because of Eylül.

112
00:09:23,280 --> 00:09:25,000
You were about to die from your illness.

113
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:26,560
You needed a kidney transplant immediately.

114
00:09:30,080 --> 00:09:31,560
You were in a very bad condition.

115
00:09:32,200 --> 00:09:33,640
There was a tissue match with Eylül.

116
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:41,520
There was no other choice but to take her kidney.

117
00:09:53,320 --> 00:09:55,200
And as a father, I did what I had to do.

118
00:10:03,360 --> 00:10:07,720
But Eylül's body was too weak. She couldn't handle the surgery.

119
00:10:08,480 --> 00:10:09,560
That's what the doctor said.

120
00:10:11,280 --> 00:10:14,280
I didn't want the poor girl to die either. I was devastated.

121
00:10:24,880 --> 00:10:25,840
But what could be done.

122
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:28,520
Who could have known this would happen.

123
00:10:29,440 --> 00:10:30,360
It was God's will.

124
00:10:40,520 --> 00:10:42,320
I saved my precious daughter.

125
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:44,760
I wish you hadn't!

126
00:10:45,840 --> 00:10:48,920
I wish you had just let me die! Let me die.

127
00:10:51,960 --> 00:10:54,560
Any father who loves his child would have done what I did.

128
00:10:54,640 --> 00:10:56,880
Do you think I can live like this!

129
00:10:56,960 --> 00:11:00,160
You killed a child, dad!

130
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:02,480
You sacrificed Eylül for me! How could you do this!

131
00:11:04,320 --> 00:11:05,720
How could you!

132
00:11:06,040 --> 00:11:08,840
She died because of me. Because of me!

133
00:11:09,440 --> 00:11:11,240
Didn't you feel any pity, none at all?

134
00:11:11,240 --> 00:11:14,720
How did your conscience not bother you! How could you do this?

135
00:11:14,760 --> 00:11:16,280
I saved your life.

136
00:11:19,280 --> 00:11:22,360
You left me at the bottom of a well.

137
00:11:23,640 --> 00:11:27,760
Knowing that I am responsible for the death of an innocent child...

138
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:30,200
How am I going to live knowing I'm a murderer.

139
00:11:42,360 --> 00:11:44,280
How am I going to carry this guilt.

140
00:12:03,240 --> 00:12:05,520
You don't have an answer, do you?

141
00:12:06,520 --> 00:12:07,400
Neither do I.

142
00:12:08,440 --> 00:12:09,400
No one does.

143
00:12:44,840 --> 00:12:46,560
(sobs uncontrollably)

144
00:12:46,560 --> 00:12:47,400
Mercan, please!

145
00:12:49,560 --> 00:12:50,320
Lift your head.

146
00:12:51,320 --> 00:12:52,160
Look into my eyes.

147
00:14:00,680 --> 00:14:02,560
What's done is done. There is nothing to do.

148
00:14:03,600 --> 00:14:04,720
It will turn out well in the end.

149
00:14:06,760 --> 00:14:08,920
You've completely lost your mind now.

150
00:14:09,520 --> 00:14:11,400
Ateş won't let you get away with this.

151
00:14:12,880 --> 00:14:14,160
And what will he do if he doesn't?

152
00:14:14,640 --> 00:14:16,600
Mercan learned everything.

153
00:14:17,240 --> 00:14:19,440
It's impossible for them to be together now.

154
00:14:20,560 --> 00:14:22,120
Is this the only thing you're thinking about?

155
00:14:22,240 --> 00:14:23,360
Them being together?

156
00:14:25,360 --> 00:14:28,240
Ateş won't let this go until he makes you pay.

157
00:14:29,920 --> 00:14:32,200
It's best if you get away from here for a few days.

158
00:14:33,160 --> 00:14:36,120
Just stay out of Ateş's sight until his anger subsides.

159
00:14:38,160 --> 00:14:39,680
I'm not going anywhere, mother!

160
00:14:40,280 --> 00:14:41,760
I'm not going to leave the field open for her.

161
00:14:42,880 --> 00:14:43,600
Besides...

162
00:14:44,440 --> 00:14:46,440
I'd like to enjoy this a little, if you don't mind.

163
00:14:48,480 --> 00:14:49,080
Idiot.

164
00:14:49,720 --> 00:14:51,760
Do you think Ateş will let you enjoy it?

165
00:14:52,680 --> 00:14:54,160
It doesn't matter at all.

166
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:55,480
I'll be by his side, that's enough for me.

167
00:14:57,520 --> 00:14:59,440
I told you a hundred times to be smart.

168
00:14:59,840 --> 00:15:01,680
Walk on snow without leaving footprints.

169
00:15:04,160 --> 00:15:07,120
Instead of waiting for the snow to fall, I just told her and that's it.

170
00:15:07,760 --> 00:15:09,120
Oh. I feel relieved.

171
00:15:45,920 --> 00:15:47,440
Did you know?

172
00:15:49,160 --> 00:15:50,480
About what?

173
00:15:51,360 --> 00:15:52,240
What's going on, my girl?

174
00:15:54,600 --> 00:15:56,280
That I am carrying Eylül's kidney.

175
00:16:00,480 --> 00:16:03,120
That she died so I could live.

176
00:16:05,720 --> 00:16:07,040
What are you talking about, Mercan?

177
00:16:07,720 --> 00:16:09,120
What kidney?

178
00:16:09,760 --> 00:16:10,880
I don't understand anything.

179
00:16:16,320 --> 00:16:17,680
Stop pretending.

180
00:16:18,080 --> 00:16:19,160
I learned everything.

181
00:16:20,440 --> 00:16:22,440
I was transplanted with Eylül's kidney.

182
00:16:23,480 --> 00:16:26,960
My father let her die so I could stay alive.

183
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:31,720
What? What are you saying?

184
00:16:33,800 --> 00:16:35,280
This can't be true, right?

185
00:16:35,760 --> 00:16:36,760
Something like this can't be.

186
00:16:38,080 --> 00:16:39,240
I didn't know, Mercan.

187
00:16:40,680 --> 00:16:41,960
I truly didn't know.

188
00:16:50,520 --> 00:16:52,920
I... I... I am so sorry.

189
00:16:58,000 --> 00:16:58,520
Let's go.

190
00:17:07,560 --> 00:17:08,840
Did you do this too, Haydar?

191
00:17:16,240 --> 00:17:17,240
He definitely did it.

192
00:17:18,440 --> 00:17:20,760
Let's not accuse anyone falsely, we'll find out anyway.

193
00:17:21,200 --> 00:17:23,800
I agree, it's not right to point fingers without knowing.

194
00:17:25,160 --> 00:17:26,000
Hello.

195
00:17:29,160 --> 00:17:32,200
Work is finally done. I'm so tired and hungry. What are we eating for dinner?

196
00:17:32,400 --> 00:17:33,560
We're preparing something.

197
00:17:42,200 --> 00:17:43,360
I can't wrap my head around this.

198
00:17:44,320 --> 00:17:46,640
Malik doesn't know anyone in this country besides us.

199
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:47,560
Isn't that right?

200
00:17:51,040 --> 00:17:54,520
He has no friends, no relatives.

201
00:17:54,880 --> 00:17:56,800
Who would report this man, and why?

202
00:18:03,560 --> 00:18:05,160
Who would cast such a slander!

203
00:18:05,800 --> 00:18:06,360
I don't know.

204
00:18:07,040 --> 00:18:14,080
It must be someone who wishes us harm, someone bursting with envy.

205
00:18:20,960 --> 00:18:22,400
Why are you looking at me like that?

206
00:18:23,640 --> 00:18:25,760
You did it, didn't you? You reported Malik.

207
00:18:25,800 --> 00:18:27,440
Are you crazy!

208
00:18:27,840 --> 00:18:29,160
Why would I report him?

209
00:18:31,280 --> 00:18:31,720
Çiçek!

210
00:18:33,760 --> 00:18:34,960
What you're doing is shameful.

211
00:18:35,800 --> 00:18:38,240
To hell with your shame! Enough!

212
00:18:38,280 --> 00:18:40,040
Your only problem is me, isn't it?

213
00:18:40,040 --> 00:18:41,640
You just want me to be sad!

214
00:18:41,680 --> 00:18:45,000
You want me to get hurt! That's why you latched onto my brother!

215
00:18:45,240 --> 00:18:48,040
Don't come at me! I said I didn't do it!

216
00:18:48,160 --> 00:18:49,120
Oh, get out of here!

217
00:18:49,160 --> 00:18:50,440
Çiçek! Sit down, both of you!

218
00:18:51,520 --> 00:18:51,960
Sit!

219
00:18:55,160 --> 00:18:55,760
Sit down, Zehra!
My God!

220
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:58,080
My God!

221
00:19:03,640 --> 00:19:04,320
What is going on!

222
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:11,160
Like children!

223
00:19:12,200 --> 00:19:14,200
I'm sorry, brother. I'm telling the truth.

224
00:19:18,360 --> 00:19:19,080
Çiçek, look...

225
00:19:20,160 --> 00:19:21,640
You're executing her without a trial.

226
00:19:28,320 --> 00:19:30,640
Çiçek, come on, let's go outside for a bit.

227
00:19:35,280 --> 00:19:36,960
Oh my God, what is happening!

228
00:19:37,440 --> 00:19:39,440
Let me go get some fresh air too, son!

229
00:19:40,320 --> 00:19:40,840
What is this?!

230
00:19:47,280 --> 00:19:48,880
-Zehra? -Hmm?

231
00:19:50,160 --> 00:19:51,720
What Çiçek said? Did you really do it?

232
00:19:53,880 --> 00:19:56,880
Look at this! Even the man I married doesn't trust me!

233
00:19:58,440 --> 00:19:59,360
It's not about not trusting you...
Shut up, Berat!

234
00:20:00,720 --> 00:20:02,440
I don't want to hear another word. Leave me alone.

235
00:20:04,320 --> 00:20:05,840
-But... -Get out, Berat!

236
00:20:06,040 --> 00:20:07,040
Leave me alone!

237
00:20:11,160 --> 00:20:12,320
The blame blew up in my face.

238
00:20:37,440 --> 00:20:38,080
Are you okay?

239
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:41,680
I'm not okay.

240
00:20:43,520 --> 00:20:44,800
I don't want to be okay either.

241
00:20:55,120 --> 00:20:56,560
I want to be alone.

242
00:20:58,240 --> 00:20:59,080
Please go.

243
00:21:04,600 --> 00:21:05,720
It's not your fault.

244
00:21:07,840 --> 00:21:11,240
Don't destroy yourself over a crime you didn't commit.

245
00:21:14,520 --> 00:21:16,720
Why do I feel guilty then?

246
00:21:21,440 --> 00:21:22,320
Get some rest, come on.

247
00:21:23,640 --> 00:21:24,520
I'll be back in a bit.

248
00:21:26,240 --> 00:21:27,520
I have something to do.

249
00:21:30,120 --> 00:21:31,880
You're going to confront Aslı, I know.

250
00:21:33,360 --> 00:21:34,320
But there's no need.

251
00:21:36,240 --> 00:21:37,480
Everything she said is true.

252
00:21:48,080 --> 00:21:49,800
Don't think about these things right now.

253
00:21:52,560 --> 00:21:53,480
I'll be right back.

254
00:22:11,640 --> 00:22:12,240
Aslı!

255
00:22:13,960 --> 00:22:14,960
Why did you do this?!

256
00:22:16,280 --> 00:22:18,600
Why did you tell Mercan everything even though I warned you?

257
00:22:19,560 --> 00:22:20,600
What do you want from her?

258
00:22:21,360 --> 00:22:22,520
What's your problem?

259
00:22:22,880 --> 00:22:23,960
What?

260
00:22:24,800 --> 00:22:27,040
My problem is that she's a murderer's daughter.

261
00:22:27,360 --> 00:22:28,120
Enough!

262
00:22:29,040 --> 00:22:30,840
You know it's not her fault.

263
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:33,920
What more do I have to do to make you listen?

264
00:22:34,680 --> 00:22:36,240
Do I have to break your heart!

265
00:22:36,480 --> 00:22:37,920
Do I have to destroy everything?

266
00:22:40,200 --> 00:22:41,760
Tell me, when are you going to stop?

267
00:22:48,720 --> 00:22:49,560
Ateş.

268
00:22:50,680 --> 00:22:53,880
I'm just trying to protect my family, protect you.

269
00:22:54,400 --> 00:22:56,160
You're not protecting anyone.

270
00:22:56,600 --> 00:23:00,560
You are hurting my wife, the woman I love.

271
00:23:01,960 --> 00:23:03,360
Don't you understand?

272
00:23:04,240 --> 00:23:07,280
That sneaky girl destroys everything she touches.

273
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:10,000
Look, we're fighting because of her.

274
00:23:10,040 --> 00:23:10,800
Don't!

275
00:23:11,680 --> 00:23:13,800
Don't let me ever hear you say such things about Mercan again.

276
00:23:14,800 --> 00:23:16,240
You will watch your mouth when talking about my wife.

277
00:23:17,320 --> 00:23:20,040
Look, I'm warning you for the last time.

278
00:23:21,440 --> 00:23:26,080
You will think fifty times before putting my wife's name in your mouth.

279
00:23:27,280 --> 00:23:29,640
If you ever do anything to hurt Mercan again...

280
00:23:30,080 --> 00:23:34,160
or do anything to upset her, know that there will be no forgiveness.

281
00:23:35,400 --> 00:23:36,240
I will erase you.

282
00:23:37,080 --> 00:23:38,120
I will erase you forever.

283
00:23:38,920 --> 00:23:40,680
You won't even go near her.

284
00:23:41,880 --> 00:23:42,840
Do you understand?

285
00:23:47,640 --> 00:23:48,880
(sobbing loudly)

286
00:23:55,240 --> 00:23:56,160
Ateş!

287
00:24:06,520 --> 00:24:07,200
Ateş...

288
00:24:13,040 --> 00:24:14,920
This Italy trip is good for you.

289
00:24:15,280 --> 00:24:16,920
Even though it's just for two days. Oh well.

290
00:24:18,520 --> 00:24:21,120
I hope I don't mess it up.

291
00:24:21,160 --> 00:24:23,080
Mr. Ateş is trusting me enough to send me for the preliminary work.

292
00:24:23,160 --> 00:24:24,440
I hope I won't let him down.

293
00:24:26,840 --> 00:24:30,560
Be careful. Don't overdo it with the pizza and pasta and get indigestion.

294
00:24:31,240 --> 00:24:33,600
I don't think I'll have time for that anyway.

295
00:24:34,960 --> 00:24:40,640
This isn't a tourist trip, Mr. Yaşar. It's a business trip. Just a reminder. Okay?

296
00:24:43,760 --> 00:24:45,080
Do you want anything from over there?

297
00:24:45,840 --> 00:24:52,000
Yes. I made a list. Don't get scared, I didn't exaggerate.

298
00:24:53,520 --> 00:24:57,200
Parmesan cheese. I want the best kind.

299
00:24:57,720 --> 00:24:59,440
Gorgonzola, that's a cheese too.

300
00:24:59,520 --> 00:25:01,840
Pasta, pizza. Pants, shoes, shirt.

301
00:25:01,960 --> 00:25:03,960
Don't forget the suspenders.

302
00:25:04,360 --> 00:25:06,600
Croissants and stuff... I wrote everything down.

303
00:25:06,600 --> 00:25:08,400
I wrote all their brands next to them.

304
00:25:09,120 --> 00:25:10,520
And he says he didn't exaggerate.

305
00:25:12,160 --> 00:25:14,840
You're the boss's son after all. I figured you wouldn't have money issues.

306
00:25:15,320 --> 00:25:16,000
Right, Burak?

307
00:25:16,880 --> 00:25:18,720
By the way, Burak... Um...

308
00:25:19,680 --> 00:25:21,760
Speaking of no money issues, it reminded me...

309
00:25:22,120 --> 00:25:26,360
There's a fountain there, the Trevi Fountain. Find it...

310
00:25:26,760 --> 00:25:30,520
Throw two euros in there for me, brother, will you?

311
00:25:31,000 --> 00:25:34,040
Maybe I'll find the love of my life, huh?

312
00:25:37,120 --> 00:25:37,840
Yaşar...

313
00:25:39,040 --> 00:25:40,600
Do you think I'm any good to myself?

314
00:25:42,520 --> 00:25:44,840
Throw two euros in for yourself then...

315
00:25:46,640 --> 00:25:46,960
Come on.

316
00:25:46,960 --> 00:25:49,080
Alright for this time, but no more...

317
00:25:50,680 --> 00:25:51,600
What does that mean?

318
00:25:53,600 --> 00:25:54,680
Do you want anything?

319
00:25:55,360 --> 00:25:58,920
Thanks, no need. Everything is available everywhere now anyway.

320
00:25:59,760 --> 00:26:01,280
I don't think there's a need either. Thanks.

321
00:26:01,760 --> 00:26:04,640
I did quite a bit of shopping when I went last summer.

322
00:26:05,080 --> 00:26:09,480
Shopping... Italy holidays and all. Sure... Wealth.

323
00:26:09,840 --> 00:26:12,600
I always forget that you're Nezir's sister.

324
00:26:12,840 --> 00:26:14,840
You're so tactless.

325
00:26:15,080 --> 00:26:16,240
Is it a lie? She's rich.

326
00:26:19,400 --> 00:26:23,080
Anyway, I should go. I'm going to pack my bags.

327
00:26:25,040 --> 00:26:26,560
And I need to not miss my flight.

328
00:26:31,840 --> 00:26:34,080
Make sure to get what I told you, okay?

329
00:26:34,680 --> 00:26:36,080
Throw coins in the fountain too.

330
00:26:37,120 --> 00:26:37,680
Okay, will do.

331
00:26:39,040 --> 00:26:39,760
Demet.

332
00:26:40,840 --> 00:26:42,920
-See you. -See you.

333
00:26:43,680 --> 00:26:44,280
Mrs. Zahide.

334
00:26:44,440 --> 00:26:46,400
See you, Burak. Call if anything happens.

335
00:26:49,520 --> 00:26:51,960
Bro, you... I asked for a belt, right?

336
00:26:52,800 --> 00:26:53,720
I'll bring it.

337
00:26:53,920 --> 00:26:55,160
I'll pray for you.

338
00:26:56,800 --> 00:26:59,000
That hurt. Lucky kid.

339
00:27:00,000 --> 00:27:01,560
I should have gone to Italy.

340
00:27:08,080 --> 00:27:10,360
My passport is nowhere to be found.

341
00:27:10,840 --> 00:27:13,680
Where did this passport disappear to.

342
00:27:14,680 --> 00:27:16,040
Couldn't you find it?

343
00:27:17,240 --> 00:27:21,480
I even checked the upper floors just in case. But no.

344
00:27:22,920 --> 00:27:23,840
I wonder where it vanished to?

345
00:27:27,960 --> 00:27:30,320
I searched every inch of the garden but couldn't find it.

346
00:27:33,480 --> 00:27:34,560
Did you find the passport?

347
00:27:35,080 --> 00:27:36,640
-No. -No.

348
00:27:37,480 --> 00:27:41,920
We left no stone unturned in this huge mansion. You'd think the ground opened up and swallowed it.

349
00:27:51,520 --> 00:27:52,840
Don't say Zehra again.

350
00:27:55,840 --> 00:27:57,760
My wife didn't do it. I'm sure of it.

351
00:28:01,920 --> 00:28:05,160
Let me check my room again. Maybe I missed it.

352
00:28:06,120 --> 00:28:06,920
See you.

353
00:28:14,640 --> 00:28:16,680
Didn't you just marry this girl?

354
00:28:17,520 --> 00:28:18,760
How can you be so sure?

355
00:28:19,720 --> 00:28:22,480
It's obvious we didn't do it.

356
00:28:23,160 --> 00:28:25,000
Well, if she didn't do it, who did?

357
00:28:25,640 --> 00:28:28,720
Her constantly nagging us about the room isn't for nothing.

358
00:28:29,320 --> 00:28:30,680
Çiçek! Don't do this.

359
00:28:31,760 --> 00:28:36,360
Let's keep searching. I think it will turn up in an unexpected place.

360
00:28:37,000 --> 00:28:38,680
You'll be ashamed of saying these things.

361
00:28:39,440 --> 00:28:40,880
-You'll see. -Sure, sure.

362
00:28:44,960 --> 00:28:46,720
Don't be too hard on your brother.

363
00:28:47,320 --> 00:28:50,080
The more you push, the closer he gets to that girl.

364
00:28:51,280 --> 00:28:52,880
You leave Zehra to me.

365
00:28:53,040 --> 00:28:55,200
I know how to deal with her.

366
00:28:59,320 --> 00:29:02,400
Running after the passport, all the chores are left undone.

367
00:29:02,760 --> 00:29:04,040
You handle the work in this kitchen.

368
00:29:04,080 --> 00:29:05,680
I'll go check the kitchen in the mansion.

369
00:29:05,800 --> 00:29:07,640
And I'll take a look around the gardens and stuff.

370
00:29:07,720 --> 00:29:08,680
-Okay mom. -Come on then.

371
00:29:09,440 --> 00:29:10,800
Leave Zehra to you, huh!

372
00:29:11,640 --> 00:29:13,120
Don't worry, I've got that covered.

373
00:29:13,440 --> 00:29:14,720
My dear mother!

374
00:29:37,800 --> 00:29:38,480
Mercan!

375
00:29:42,280 --> 00:29:42,920
Mercan!

376
00:29:54,360 --> 00:29:55,600
Are you better? I was worried about you.

377
00:29:59,880 --> 00:30:01,440
I won't be okay for a while.

378
00:30:32,080 --> 00:30:32,880
You'll get sick.

379
00:30:36,040 --> 00:30:37,160
What difference does it make?

380
00:30:40,240 --> 00:30:41,720
You just found out too, didn't you?

381
00:30:48,880 --> 00:30:49,520
Yes.

382
00:30:53,200 --> 00:30:54,920
You knew when you came to the cemetery.

383
00:30:59,040 --> 00:31:02,800
That's why you ran away, distanced yourself from me.

384
00:31:04,800 --> 00:31:06,200
Why didn't you just tell me openly?

385
00:31:08,160 --> 00:31:09,280
I didn't want you to be devastated.

386
00:31:12,200 --> 00:31:12,920
So you wouldn't be sad.

387
00:31:16,840 --> 00:31:17,640
You were right.

388
00:31:19,840 --> 00:31:21,280
-Mercan... -You were right.

389
00:31:22,920 --> 00:31:26,560
You were right when you said we couldn't be together.

390
00:31:37,720 --> 00:31:40,640
It's true, this love must end.

391
00:31:42,040 --> 00:31:43,760
I can't blame you for this.

392
00:31:45,880 --> 00:31:46,920
That's why you said it.

393
00:32:18,240 --> 00:32:18,880
Eylül...

394
00:32:20,840 --> 00:32:21,480
Eylül...

395
00:32:22,920 --> 00:32:25,200
I became her murderer without knowing.

396
00:32:26,960 --> 00:32:27,720
Eylül...

397
00:32:38,960 --> 00:32:40,160
Don't say such things.

398
00:32:44,440 --> 00:32:45,840
You are not a murderer.

399
00:32:49,200 --> 00:32:50,160
You were a child too.

400
00:32:56,600 --> 00:32:57,520
While I'm alive...

401
00:32:59,080 --> 00:33:01,880
what could be more wrong than Eylül being dead.

402
00:33:05,520 --> 00:33:09,680
Your sister should be alive and I should be in the grave. That was the truth.

403
00:33:10,920 --> 00:33:12,040
Mercan, please.

404
00:33:18,720 --> 00:33:19,200
How...

405
00:33:22,200 --> 00:33:25,520
How did you endure all this pain?

406
00:33:29,960 --> 00:33:30,600
Because this...

407
00:33:31,720 --> 00:33:33,240
This isn't a pain one can bear.

408
00:33:47,280 --> 00:33:48,160
I'll be right back.

409
00:34:42,440 --> 00:34:43,800
I'm so sorry.

410
00:34:49,160 --> 00:34:50,160
I am so sorry.

411
00:34:53,440 --> 00:34:56,680
I wish that so I could live, you didn't...

412
00:34:59,160 --> 00:35:00,000
I apologize.

413
00:35:04,440 --> 00:35:05,520
I apologize.

414
00:35:46,440 --> 00:35:47,080
My Ateş...

415
00:35:57,240 --> 00:35:59,440
I know you're burning in roaring flames.

416
00:36:04,280 --> 00:36:05,560
I am so sorry.

417
00:36:07,120 --> 00:36:08,040
I am so sorry.

418
00:36:15,000 --> 00:36:16,240
I am so sorry.

419
00:36:58,160 --> 00:37:00,360
(singing)

420
00:37:19,040 --> 00:37:20,320
(continues singing)

421
00:37:38,320 --> 00:37:39,040
What are you doing?

422
00:37:43,160 --> 00:37:44,440
I'm going to take something to eat to Ateş and Mercan.

423
00:37:45,400 --> 00:37:46,920
I remembered when you mentioned it.

424
00:37:47,360 --> 00:37:48,560
I haven't eaten much today either.

425
00:37:49,920 --> 00:37:51,120
-Mercan... -Take your hand off.

426
00:37:54,840 --> 00:37:55,720
What's wrong with you?

427
00:37:56,760 --> 00:37:58,880
Do you care about that girl more than me too?

428
00:37:59,000 --> 00:38:00,120
What does that have to do with anything?

429
00:38:01,600 --> 00:38:03,040
If you had asked, I would have prepared something for you too.

430
00:38:03,600 --> 00:38:05,800
But you set your eyes on her food.

431
00:38:12,200 --> 00:38:14,320
Seeing this side of you hurts a person inside.

432
00:38:15,560 --> 00:38:17,160
I just got my daily scolding from my mother.

433
00:38:17,560 --> 00:38:19,240
I have no intention of getting another one.

434
00:38:26,000 --> 00:38:27,680
People are telling you things.

435
00:38:29,040 --> 00:38:31,160
I wish you'd listen to what you're being told. What do you say?

436
00:38:33,040 --> 00:38:35,200
I'm trying to protect Ateş from that girl.

437
00:38:36,040 --> 00:38:37,880
Aslı, what are you tripping on? What protection?

438
00:38:38,360 --> 00:38:39,640
Who is asking you for this?

439
00:38:40,400 --> 00:38:42,200
No one needs to ask.

440
00:38:42,600 --> 00:38:43,520
I want to.

441
00:38:44,080 --> 00:38:45,080
So you want to, huh?

442
00:38:47,240 --> 00:38:49,040
Are you aware of what you're doing?

443
00:38:50,760 --> 00:38:51,640
Of your behavior and all?

444
00:38:52,520 --> 00:38:54,360
Aslı, why don't you get off the backs of people in love?

445
00:38:55,240 --> 00:38:56,080
Cemal, enough!

446
00:38:57,080 --> 00:38:58,240
Watch how you speak to me.

447
00:38:59,160 --> 00:39:01,320
Am I going to learn what to do from you?

448
00:39:04,840 --> 00:39:05,360
What?

449
00:39:06,400 --> 00:39:07,600
Why are you looking at me like that?

450
00:39:09,240 --> 00:39:10,880
Someone I've valued for so long...

451
00:39:11,880 --> 00:39:13,760
I suddenly realized she didn't deserve this value at all.

452
00:39:18,160 --> 00:39:19,880
I'm in no mood to listen to advice.

453
00:39:21,080 --> 00:39:23,560
Good luck to you, good person.

454
00:39:35,240 --> 00:39:35,840
Haydar!

455
00:39:37,080 --> 00:39:38,000
Can you hear me?

456
00:39:42,160 --> 00:39:42,880
Yes.

457
00:39:46,480 --> 00:39:49,960
Mercan said some things about Eylül.

458
00:39:51,840 --> 00:39:52,800
Is what she said true?

459
00:39:54,240 --> 00:39:54,760
Did you...

460
00:39:56,240 --> 00:39:59,920
Did you really sacrifice that girl so Mercan could live?

461
00:40:03,120 --> 00:40:03,840
Yes. I did.

462
00:40:04,200 --> 00:40:05,560
I'm not ashamed of what I did.

463
00:40:05,920 --> 00:40:06,720
And I'm not regretful.

464
00:40:09,880 --> 00:40:11,360
I can't wrap my head around it.

465
00:40:11,960 --> 00:40:13,880
How could you do such a thing?

466
00:40:16,040 --> 00:40:18,360
The only thing you weren't was a child murderer. Now you're that too.

467
00:40:20,760 --> 00:40:22,640
Even I wouldn't have expected this much from you.

468
00:40:23,280 --> 00:40:24,600
I didn't kill her.

469
00:40:25,360 --> 00:40:26,520
She couldn't handle the surgery.

470
00:40:27,600 --> 00:40:28,680
That's not my fault.

471
00:40:29,800 --> 00:40:32,160
Besides, is that girl more precious than Mercan?

472
00:40:33,000 --> 00:40:34,440
What difference did she have from a stray dog?

473
00:40:34,800 --> 00:40:35,920
What's going to happen now?

474
00:40:37,960 --> 00:40:40,960
Ateş won't let you go without avenging his sister.

475
00:40:42,000 --> 00:40:43,000
What if he goes to the police?

476
00:40:44,680 --> 00:40:46,520
If you go to jail, what will I do?

477
00:40:48,320 --> 00:40:51,480
Not only will I be disgraced in society, my life will be over.

478
00:40:53,240 --> 00:40:54,720
Where will I go, penniless?

479
00:40:54,920 --> 00:40:56,160
What will I eat, what will I drink?

480
00:40:58,120 --> 00:41:01,280
You are the most selfish person I know.

481
00:41:02,000 --> 00:41:03,600
Even in this situation, you're only thinking of yourself.

482
00:41:04,280 --> 00:41:05,000
What was I supposed to do, tell me?

483
00:41:05,280 --> 00:41:08,320
Should I have just stood by and watched Haydar Yıldırım's daughter die?

484
00:41:09,800 --> 00:41:11,160
I did what I had to do.

485
00:41:12,920 --> 00:41:15,560
So the issue is her being Haydar Yıldırım's daughter?

486
00:41:16,160 --> 00:41:16,800
Yes!

487
00:41:18,080 --> 00:41:19,480
Her being my daughter, yes.

488
00:41:21,920 --> 00:41:25,200
You know it too. I tried every way. I knocked on every door.

489
00:41:25,800 --> 00:41:27,360
I couldn't find any other solution.

490
00:41:28,320 --> 00:41:30,800
Alright. Alright, I know.

491
00:41:30,960 --> 00:41:31,480
You...

492
00:41:32,880 --> 00:41:35,280
Whatever you did, you did it for Mercan, that's true.

493
00:41:36,160 --> 00:41:37,520
Even if the consequences are very heavy.

494
00:41:38,680 --> 00:41:40,280
But... But still...

495
00:41:40,800 --> 00:41:42,760
But there is still a dead child in the middle of this.

496
00:41:45,080 --> 00:41:45,760
Look, Nermin...

497
00:41:46,320 --> 00:41:47,960
This is not the time to be at each other's throats.

498
00:41:48,920 --> 00:41:50,800
Since you're so afraid of this man's wrath,

499
00:41:51,120 --> 00:41:54,200
you need to get me out of here as urgently as possible.

500
00:41:54,640 --> 00:41:56,160
Fine, but how?

501
00:41:57,280 --> 00:41:59,040
What can I possibly do all by myself as a woman?

502
00:41:59,400 --> 00:42:00,200
I don't know.

503
00:42:00,480 --> 00:42:02,760
Ask Nezir for help. Just do something.

504
00:42:02,920 --> 00:42:05,640
I'm going to die between these four walls. I'm suffocating.

505
00:42:06,880 --> 00:42:07,520
Okay.

506
00:42:08,840 --> 00:42:09,840
Okay.

507
00:42:39,280 --> 00:42:41,080
Neither of you has taken a single bite.

508
00:42:41,360 --> 00:42:42,800
I prepared something for you to eat.

509
00:42:43,280 --> 00:42:44,240
You shouldn't have gone to the trouble.

510
00:42:45,360 --> 00:42:46,840
What trouble? Don't mention it.

511
00:42:48,080 --> 00:42:49,000
How is Mercan?

512
00:42:50,640 --> 00:42:51,840
Not good at all. Very sad.

513
00:42:54,800 --> 00:42:56,440
If you need anything, just say the word.

514
00:42:57,560 --> 00:42:58,920
I'll do whatever I can.

515
00:42:59,640 --> 00:43:01,160
I know. Thanks.

516
00:43:09,560 --> 00:43:10,080
Mercan.

517
00:43:11,440 --> 00:43:14,600
Cemal made food. Come let's eat.

518
00:43:15,400 --> 00:43:16,320
I don't feel like it.

519
00:43:17,280 --> 00:43:18,320
You can't go on like this, though.

520
00:43:18,840 --> 00:43:20,280
Your immune system is already weak. You'll get sick.

521
00:43:21,120 --> 00:43:22,160
Please get up. Don't let the food get cold.

522
00:43:24,760 --> 00:43:26,200
You're not going to give up, are you?

523
00:43:28,760 --> 00:43:29,400
I won't.

524
00:43:31,160 --> 00:43:32,240
Because I don't want you to get sick.

525
00:43:39,680 --> 00:43:40,400
Open your mouth.

526
00:43:44,760 --> 00:43:45,600
I have no appetite at all.

527
00:43:49,000 --> 00:43:49,880
Force yourself a little.

528
00:43:51,000 --> 00:43:53,040
You need to take your medicine. It's almost time.

529
00:43:54,760 --> 00:43:55,480
I don't want it!

530
00:43:58,200 --> 00:44:00,280
I won't take my medicine from now on either.

531
00:44:01,520 --> 00:44:03,640
You can't do that. You know that, right?

532
00:44:05,240 --> 00:44:06,600
You know you have to take that medicine every day.

533
00:44:10,000 --> 00:44:13,240
The nicer you act, the more my guilty conscience grows.

534
00:44:15,120 --> 00:44:16,040
Please, don't do this to yourself!

535
00:44:17,960 --> 00:44:19,800
Tormenting yourself won't do any good.

536
00:44:21,560 --> 00:44:23,840
I know the burden on your shoulders is very heavy.

537
00:44:23,880 --> 00:44:26,360
No, you can't know.

538
00:44:30,080 --> 00:44:32,840
I feel like I'm breathing breaths that don't belong to me.

539
00:44:34,880 --> 00:44:37,600
It's as if I'm living a life that doesn't belong to me.

540
00:44:42,760 --> 00:44:45,160
The guilt is destroying me.

541
00:44:46,920 --> 00:44:48,640
I'm in so much pain.

542
00:44:53,400 --> 00:44:55,840
Do you realize how selfishly you're acting right now?

543
00:44:57,840 --> 00:45:00,200
If you look around, you'll see you're not the only one suffering.

544
00:45:03,160 --> 00:45:04,720
You asked me how I endure it.

545
00:45:10,280 --> 00:45:10,920
I can't.

546
00:45:13,560 --> 00:45:15,200
My heart is burning in flames.

547
00:45:22,160 --> 00:45:23,440
I lost my little sister.

548
00:45:28,880 --> 00:45:30,040
I lost my precious one.

549
00:45:38,120 --> 00:45:41,040
If I am staying quiet, if I am being patient, it's for you.

550
00:45:50,640 --> 00:45:52,200
The more I see you doing this injustice to yourself...

551
00:45:53,920 --> 00:45:57,040
my sorrow multiplies, my conscience aches.

552
00:46:02,520 --> 00:46:03,280
Please don't do this to me.

553
00:46:06,680 --> 00:46:07,840
I can't bear this.

554
00:46:12,720 --> 00:46:14,000
Forgive me, Ateş.

555
00:46:22,280 --> 00:46:24,040
Forgive me, I beg you.

556
00:46:34,120 --> 00:46:34,800
Forgive me, I beg you.

557
00:46:36,760 --> 00:46:38,440
You haven't done anything to be forgiven for.

558
00:49:32,880 --> 00:49:33,520
Mercan?

559
00:49:53,120 --> 00:49:53,680
Mercan?

560
00:50:18,360 --> 00:50:19,440
You must be cold.

561
00:50:19,640 --> 00:50:20,760
I brought you some tea.

562
00:50:21,040 --> 00:50:21,920
Drink this and warm up a bit.
Thanks.

563
00:50:23,760 --> 00:50:24,560
Thank you.

564
00:50:28,640 --> 00:50:29,560
There is nowhere left I haven't looked.

565
00:50:29,880 --> 00:50:31,320
I checked every hole and corner.

566
00:50:32,120 --> 00:50:34,000
But no. It's nowhere.

567
00:50:35,400 --> 00:50:37,520
So are they going to send you back to your country now?

568
00:50:37,760 --> 00:50:39,240
I don't know what they're going to do either.

569
00:50:39,720 --> 00:50:41,240
Maybe there is a solution.

570
00:50:42,960 --> 00:50:43,960
What if there isn't?

571
00:50:44,600 --> 00:50:46,240
Let's not think about bad things.

572
00:50:47,000 --> 00:50:47,920
There is a solution.

573
00:50:48,040 --> 00:50:51,320
I just need to gather my thoughts a bit.

574
00:50:51,320 --> 00:50:53,680
If I think, maybe I'll remember where I put it.

575
00:50:54,320 --> 00:50:56,000
And I am saying...

576
00:50:57,280 --> 00:50:59,680
Well... Like, if you can't find it...

577
00:51:00,560 --> 00:51:02,440
If you have to go...

578
00:51:05,880 --> 00:51:07,240
I'll come with you too.

579
00:51:08,280 --> 00:51:09,080
What do you mean?

580
00:51:10,600 --> 00:51:11,400
Just that.

581
00:51:12,040 --> 00:51:12,760
Really?

582
00:51:14,000 --> 00:51:14,800
Really.

583
00:51:28,200 --> 00:51:29,240
But how is that going to work?

584
00:51:31,640 --> 00:51:33,360
Aunt Binnaz won't allow it.

585
00:51:35,880 --> 00:51:37,280
I talked to my mom.

586
00:51:38,320 --> 00:51:40,920
She understood how great our love is too.

587
00:51:41,240 --> 00:51:43,040
She doesn't have the heart to let us be apart.

588
00:51:46,360 --> 00:51:49,480
I don't know where or how our tomorrow will be.

589
00:51:51,240 --> 00:51:52,280
Our destinies are written as one.

590
00:51:52,880 --> 00:51:53,560
I am sure of that.

591
00:51:55,120 --> 00:51:56,680
Don't ever leave me without you.

592
00:51:58,880 --> 00:51:59,600
You too.

593
00:52:11,480 --> 00:52:12,000
Cemal!

594
00:52:13,320 --> 00:52:14,240
Have you seen Mercan?

595
00:52:15,160 --> 00:52:16,720
No, I haven't. Did something happen?

596
00:52:18,640 --> 00:52:19,480
She's not in the room.

597
00:52:20,600 --> 00:52:22,520
Don't worry, she's probably in the garden. She might have gone for a walk.

598
00:52:22,920 --> 00:52:24,520
I don't know Cemal, she wasn't well at all.

599
00:52:24,720 --> 00:52:26,520
Okay, calm down. We'll find her now.

600
00:52:45,720 --> 00:52:46,840
Did Mrs. Mercan leave the mansion?

601
00:52:46,880 --> 00:52:48,120
Mrs. Mercan left early.

602
00:52:48,280 --> 00:52:49,520
I called out to her, but she didn't hear at all.

603
00:52:50,600 --> 00:52:51,240
What do you mean?

604
00:52:52,160 --> 00:52:53,240
How could you allow this?

605
00:52:53,520 --> 00:52:55,560
Ateş, wait, calm down, how could they know?

606
00:52:57,920 --> 00:52:58,880
Did she take a car?

607
00:52:59,400 --> 00:53:00,200
No, on foot.

608
00:53:01,840 --> 00:53:03,280
Cemal, you guys keep looking around.

609
00:53:03,360 --> 00:53:05,000
Okay. I'll send a few of the men outside too.

610
00:53:19,200 --> 00:53:20,880
I dropped everything and came as soon as you told me to come.

611
00:53:21,600 --> 00:53:22,640
I hope it's really something important.

612
00:53:23,360 --> 00:53:25,120
It's important. It really is.

613
00:53:26,960 --> 00:53:27,880
Did something happen to Mercan?

614
00:53:28,920 --> 00:53:29,720
Mercan is fine.

615
00:53:30,720 --> 00:53:31,960
For now.

616
00:53:33,040 --> 00:53:33,880
What does this mean?

617
00:53:34,960 --> 00:53:35,640
Nezir...

618
00:53:36,520 --> 00:53:38,400
None of us are safe in this mansion anymore.

619
00:53:41,040 --> 00:53:43,280
Haydar is still locked in the basement.

620
00:53:44,280 --> 00:53:45,560
And there's nothing I can do.

621
00:53:46,440 --> 00:53:47,680
Please help us.

622
00:53:51,040 --> 00:53:52,640
I offered Mercan help.

623
00:53:53,720 --> 00:53:55,000
I even said it for you too.

624
00:53:55,720 --> 00:53:56,320
She didn't want it.

625
00:53:58,920 --> 00:54:00,400
Oh Mercan, oh.

626
00:54:02,200 --> 00:54:03,400
But we are not the subject right now.

627
00:54:06,480 --> 00:54:07,880
You can get Haydar out of that basement.

628
00:54:09,320 --> 00:54:10,560
What will be my gain from this?

629
00:54:11,920 --> 00:54:14,600
Him getting out or not means nothing to Mercan.

630
00:54:16,400 --> 00:54:17,760
What do you mean?

631
00:54:19,520 --> 00:54:20,960
Are you saying you won't help me?

632
00:54:21,640 --> 00:54:22,480
Mrs. Nermin.

633
00:54:23,840 --> 00:54:25,760
You call me every time you're in a tight spot.

634
00:54:26,560 --> 00:54:28,920
I'm tired of being your panic button.

635
00:54:31,600 --> 00:54:33,200
We've been friends for so many years.

636
00:54:34,400 --> 00:54:35,720
Are you going to turn your back on me?

637
00:54:35,920 --> 00:54:37,320
You turned your back on me too.

638
00:54:39,080 --> 00:54:41,480
I tore myself apart so Mercan wouldn't marry Ateş.

639
00:54:42,800 --> 00:54:43,480
But you...

640
00:54:44,400 --> 00:54:45,520
didn't care about me at all.

641
00:54:46,440 --> 00:54:47,920
You even supported that marriage.

642
00:54:52,040 --> 00:54:52,600
Look...

643
00:54:54,720 --> 00:54:56,520
There is only one person I care about.

644
00:54:56,840 --> 00:54:57,680
And that's Mercan.

645
00:54:58,880 --> 00:55:00,600
And I'm already doing what's necessary for her.

646
00:55:03,800 --> 00:55:05,760
What happens to you anymore doesn't concern me.

647
00:55:11,760 --> 00:55:12,240
Ah...

648
00:55:13,480 --> 00:55:17,200
If there's an issue concerning Mercan, then you can call me anytime.

649
00:55:20,360 --> 00:55:21,320
I don't know if I made myself clear?

650
00:55:33,840 --> 00:55:36,760
If you ask them, they're pure as the driven snow, and I'm the bad one.

651
00:55:37,840 --> 00:55:40,760
If they're so good, why did they become enemies to me.

652
00:55:42,560 --> 00:55:45,800
Do they have proof that they're accusing me.

653
00:55:47,760 --> 00:55:49,480
If they weren't ashamed, they'd execute me.

654
00:55:49,920 --> 00:55:52,200
But they don't know how cunning I am.

655
00:55:53,200 --> 00:55:55,520
They'll see who's boss.

656
00:55:56,480 --> 00:55:58,400
This knife won't cut either!

657
00:55:59,360 --> 00:56:00,280
Where is the other one?

658
00:56:10,320 --> 00:56:13,480
God knows that Çiçek hid it just to annoy me.

659
00:56:23,920 --> 00:56:24,480
What is this?

660
00:56:34,840 --> 00:56:36,880
Aha! Malik's passport is here.

661
00:56:39,000 --> 00:56:40,320
And they accused me.

662
00:56:43,040 --> 00:56:44,160
Have you fallen into my hands?

663
00:56:46,680 --> 00:56:48,440
Let's see what you'll do now.

664
00:57:09,480 --> 00:57:11,120
Hello? What is it now?

665
00:57:14,680 --> 00:57:15,520
Which hospital?

666
00:57:18,760 --> 00:57:19,680
How much did you say?

667
00:57:24,320 --> 00:57:25,120
I understand, okay.

668
00:57:27,760 --> 00:57:29,920
I'll pay the hospital, not you.

669
00:57:32,040 --> 00:57:33,520
I just sent you money recently.

670
00:57:36,840 --> 00:57:39,240
No. Don't drag it out, okay. I'll pay the hospital bills.

671
00:57:40,120 --> 00:57:42,200
Come on, come on. I'm busy, we'll talk later.

672
00:58:32,400 --> 00:58:33,240
I was worried sick.

673
00:58:35,000 --> 00:58:36,400
What are you doing out in this freezing cold.

674
00:58:40,040 --> 00:58:41,000
You found me again.

675
00:58:45,800 --> 00:58:47,360
Wherever you go, I will find you.

676
00:58:54,440 --> 00:58:56,400
You know very well what makes me feel better.

677
00:59:15,400 --> 00:59:16,560
Look how the seagull snatched the simit, did you see?

678
00:59:18,120 --> 00:59:18,640
I saw.

679
00:59:22,520 --> 00:59:23,400
They're hungry.

680
00:59:38,160 --> 00:59:39,720
I can't get over this, Ateş.

681
00:59:42,040 --> 00:59:44,120
I don't know how I'm going to continue my life.

682
00:59:51,960 --> 00:59:53,120
We will continue together.

683
00:59:55,560 --> 00:59:56,480
I'm in so much pain.

684
00:59:59,080 --> 01:00:01,600
I don't know how one lives with this pain.

685
01:00:06,960 --> 01:00:08,600
Everything started because of me.

686
01:00:12,080 --> 01:00:13,240
All these things that happened...

687
01:00:15,400 --> 01:00:16,880
the pain that was suffered,

688
01:00:18,520 --> 01:00:19,480
your vow of revenge...

689
01:00:23,200 --> 01:00:23,800
Even...

690
01:00:24,720 --> 01:00:26,520
even my brother's death is because of me.

691
01:00:31,040 --> 01:00:31,720
That day...

692
01:00:33,920 --> 01:00:35,520
If I had died instead of Eylül...

693
01:00:37,120 --> 01:00:38,560
-none of this would have happened... -Enough.

694
01:00:41,080 --> 01:00:41,960
Stop doing this.

695
01:00:47,520 --> 01:00:48,520
To yourself and to me.

696
01:00:53,440 --> 01:00:55,920
I'm lost as to what to think or what to feel anymore.

697
01:01:00,360 --> 01:01:01,480
There is no consolation for this pain.

698
01:01:07,920 --> 01:01:09,480
It won't pass until the day I die, I know.

699
01:01:14,960 --> 01:01:16,160
You are the only thing I have left.

700
01:01:25,680 --> 01:01:26,480
Everything else is a lie.

701
01:01:28,440 --> 01:01:29,320
Everything is empty.

702
01:01:43,280 --> 01:01:44,760
And I don't want to lose you too.

703
01:01:55,240 --> 01:01:56,400
Your cheeks are freezing cold.

704
01:01:57,280 --> 01:01:58,440
Come on, let's go back to our home so you don't get sick.

705
01:02:10,800 --> 01:02:11,360
Mercan!

706
01:02:17,080 --> 01:02:17,680
Mercan!

707
01:02:20,600 --> 01:02:21,560
Mercan, open your eyes!
